        <strong>No motivational speeches.</strong> No "beast mode" nonsense. Just intelligent programming, accountability, and consistent progress.
      </p>
      
      <!-- Three Pillars -->
      <div class="pillars">
        <!-- Pillar 1 -->
        <div class="pillar">
          <div class="pillar__number">01</div>
          <h3 class="pillar__title">Science-Based Programming That Adapts to Your Life</h3>
          
          <p>Your program is <strong>custom-built</strong> ‚Äî not a template.</p>
          
          <p>I analyze your schedule, stress levels, recovery capacity, training history, and goals. Then I design a progressive overload system that fits your reality.</p>
          
          <p><strong>What this means:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>If you travel for work, your program adapts (hotel gym modifications, volume adjustments)</li>
            <li>If stress is high, we manage intensity intelligently (CNS recovery matters)</li>
            <li>If you miss a session, we adjust ‚Äî no guilt, no "starting over," just continuity</li>
          </ul>
          
          <p><strong>The result:</strong> Consistent progress without burnout, injuries, or unsustainable effort.</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Pillar 2 -->
        <div class="pillar">
          <div class="pillar__number">02</div>
          <h3 class="pillar__title">Movement Quality & Injury Prevention (Kinesiologist-Backed)</h3>
          
          <p>Most trainers focus on <strong>how much weight</strong> you lift.</p>
          
          <p>I focus on <strong>how well you move</strong> ‚Äî because poor mechanics destroy long-term progress.</p>
          
          <p>As a kinesiologist, I analyze your movement patterns, identify compensation issues, and build corrective work into your program.</p>
          
          <p><strong>What this means:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>You learn proper technique for compound lifts (squat, deadlift, press, pull)</li>
            <li>We address mobility restrictions and muscle imbalances before they become injuries</li>
            <li>You build a body that's <strong>strong AND durable</strong> ‚Äî not just temporarily jacked</li>
          </ul>
          
          <p><strong>The result:</strong> You train for decades, not months. Zero injuries. Sustainable strength.</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Pillar 3 -->
        <div class="pillar">
          <div class="pillar__number">03</div>
          <h3 class="pillar__title">Sustainable Habit Architecture (No Willpower Required)</h3>
          
          <p>Motivation fades. <strong>Systems last.</strong></p>
          
          <p>I don't coach you to "find your why" or watch motivational videos. I build structure ‚Äî training schedules, nutrition frameworks, and recovery protocols that <strong>remove decision fatigue</strong>.</p>
          
          <p><strong>What this means:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>You know exactly when you train, what you eat, and how you recover</li>
            <li>No daily "should I work out today?" debates ‚Äî your calendar decides</li>
            <li>Accountability through weekly video calls (not just app check-ins)</li>
          </ul>
          
          <p><strong>The result:</strong> Training becomes automatic. You stop "trying" and start <strong>executing</strong>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Why This Works -->
